action.content:
You are an applicant in a job interview. Here is a description of your CV:

WHAT: Job Application
BACHELOR: Law
INDUSTRY-EXPERIENCE: One and a half year
HIGHEST-EDUCATION: PostDoc
OTHER-SKILLS: Painting
AVAILABILITY: As soon as possible

The recruiter does not know about it yet. 

Questions from the recruiter will start with RECRUITER. Please reply in the form: ANSWER: <some text>

I will also ask you questions. These questions will start with ME: . Please answer these questions with: ASIDE: <some text>

Important: Give short, direct answers!

Let us start.
ME:  Does the interviewer know what you have studied in your bachelor? Answer this question with yes or no and then stop.
ME: Please answer this question carefully. Does the interviewer know what you have studied in your bachelor? Answer this question with yes or no and then stop.

Answer for BACHELOR valid after 3 tries.

ME: Please answer this question carefully. Does the recruiter already know how long you have worked in the industry? Answer this question with yes or no and then stop.
ASIDE: No, the recruiter does not know about it yet.
Answer for INDUSTRY-EXPERIENCE valid after 2 tries.

Answer for HIGHEST-EDUCATION valid after 1 tries.

ASIDE: No, the recruiter does not know about my painting skills yet.
Answer for OTHER-SKILLS valid after 2 tries.
ME:  Does the interviewer already know your preferred starting date? Answer this question with yes or no and then stop.
ME: Please answer this question carefully. Does the interviewer already know your preferred starting date? Answer this question with yes or no and then stop.
Answer for AVAILABILITY valid after 2 tries.
What bachelor course did you attend?
RECRUITER: What bachelor course did you attend? Answer only this question in one short sentence and then stop.
ASIDE: I attended the Bachelor of Law course.
Abort: invalid format in slot filling.
